    <note>Song Wo [7066] He moved from Guangping jun (Mingzhou[b]) where the Song(2) were a distinguished lineage (zhuxing) to Henan, Luoyang xian. Wu's wife, born Liu, was a daughter of one of the Later Han emperors. Guangping jun Song(2) Yanzhao [3808], the father-in-law of Xiang(2) Minzhong [705] (qv.), was probably his uncle. Zhao(1) Taizu's [9001], Zhang(1) Xun(1)'s [232], Han(1) Chongxun's [8048], Cao(1) Shourang's [7356] and Dong(1) Sixian's [7368] father-in-law, and Zhao(1) Conggu's [7180] grandfather-in-law. Kou(1) Zhun's [898] affinal kin of the same generation [on the basis of generational names]. Wang Yucheng, WJ, 28.1a-19b (funerary inscription by imperial edict). CBD, 1, 745-6.</note>
